   200→- Day 1-2: LTI 1.1 launch + OAuth validation
   201→- Day 3: Room creation via LTI context
   202→- Day 4: Role-based routing (teacher/student)
   203→- Day 5: Mock quiz display in Electron
   204→- Day 6: Grade passback (mock score)
   205→- Day 7: Replace mock with real Quiz API (if time allows)
   206→
   207→## Recommended Approach: Parallel Implementation (Approach A)
   208→
   209→This is the highest-risk approach but the only one that fits everything into 7 days. Sequential approaches are too slow for the deadline, and the mock approach fails the "full integration" requirement.
   210→
   211→**Why this works:**
   212→- LTI launch and Quiz fetch are mostly independent
   213→- Can demo progress early (Day 2 LTI, Day 4 Quiz)
   214→- Integration happens when both tracks are mature
   215→- Parallel development maximizes calendar time
   216→
   217→**Risk mitigation:**
   218→- Define clear API contracts between LTI and Quiz tracks
   219→- Use integration tests from Day 1
   220→- Daily sync on interface compatibility
   221→- Fallback: if Quiz track lags, use placeholder content
   222→
   223→## Implementation Plan
   224→
   225→**CRITICAL WARNINGS:**
   226→1. **OAuth 1.0 signature debugging is notoriously painful** — Expect 1-2 days just for this. Common issues: timestamp drift, URL encoding, base64 normalization.
   227→2. **ltijs library compatibility** — ltijs primarily supports LTI 1.3. For LTI 1.1, you may need `ltijs` with legacy provider or use a different library like `ims-lti`.
   228→3. **Moodle Quiz state machine** — Quiz attempts have complex states (inprogress, overdue, abandoned, finished). Handle transitions properly or submissions will fail.
   229→4. **Electron sandbox breaks localStorage** — If you enable `sandbox: true`, you can't use `localStorage` in renderer. Use `sessionStorage` or implement IPC to main process.
   230→
   231→**Scope for survival:**
   232→- Implement ONLY essay (textarea) and multiple-choice (radio) questions
   233→- Cut teacher LTI integration (use existing dashboard)
   234→- Cut XML cartridge (configure tool manually in Moodle)
   235→- Binary grade passback (pass=1.0, fail=0.0) — actual scores are post-deadline
   236→
   237→### Phase 1: LTI 1.1 Backend (Days 1-2)
   238→
   239→**1.1 Install LTI library**
   240→
   241→```bash
   242→cd backend
   243→npm install ims-lti@latest
   244→```
   245→
   246→**CRITICAL:** Use `ims-lti` (NOT `ltijs`) — `ims-lti` has stable LTI 1.1 support with OAuth 1.0 validation. `ltijs` primarily targets LTI 1.3 and has unstable LTI 1.1 support.
   247→
   248→**1.2 Create LTI provider setup**
   249→
   250→Create `backend/src/modules/lti/lti.service.ts`:
   251→
   252→```typescript
   253→import { Provider } from 'ims-lti';
   254→import crypto from 'crypto';
   255→import logger from '../../config/logger';
   256→
   257→// LTI 1.1 Provider setup
   258→const provider = new Provider(
   259→  process.env.LTI_CONSUMER_KEY || 'moodle',
   260→  process.env.LTI_CONSUMER_SECRET || 'secret',
   261→  {
   262→    signature_method: 'HMAC-SHA1',
   263→    nonce: () => crypto.randomBytes(16).toString('base64'),
   264→    timestamp: () => Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000).toString()
   265→  }
   266→);
   267→
   268→/**
   269→ * Validate LTI 1.1 launch request (OAuth 1.0 signature)
   270→ */
   271→export async function validateLaunch(body: any): Promise<boolean> {
   272→  try {
   273→    // Extract OAuth parameters from body
   274→    const oauthSignature = body.oauth_signature;
   275→    const oauthTimestamp = body.oauth_timestamp;
   276→    const oauthNonce = body.oauth_nonce;
   277→    const oauthConsumerKey = body.oauth_consumer_key;
   278→    const oauthVersion = body.oauth_version;
   279→
   280→    // Basic validation
   281→    if (!oauthSignature || !oauthTimestamp || !oauthNonce || !oauthConsumerKey) {
   282→      logger.error('Missing OAuth parameters');
   283→      return false;
   284→    }
   285→
   286→    // Check timestamp is within 5 minutes (prevent replay attacks)
   287→    const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);
   288→    if (Math.abs(now - parseInt(oauthTimestamp, 10)) > 300) {
   289→      logger.error('OAuth timestamp too old', { oauthTimestamp, now });
   290→      return false;
   291→    }
   292→
   293→    // Validate signature using ims-lti provider
   294→    const valid = await provider.valid_request(body);
   295→
   296→    if (!valid) {
   297→      logger.error('Invalid OAuth signature');
   298→      return false;
   299→    }
   300→
   301→    logger.info('LTI launch validated successfully');
   302→    return true;
   303→
   304→  } catch (error) {
   305→    logger.error('LTI validation error:', error);
   306→    return false;
   307→  }
   308→}
   309→
   310→export default { validateLaunch };
   311→```
   312→
   313→**1.3 Create LTI launch endpoint**
   314→
   315→Create `backend/src/modules/lti/lti.routes.ts`:
   316→
   317→```typescript
   318→import { FastifyInstance, FastifyReply } from 'fastify';
   319→import jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';
   320→import { validateLaunch } from './lti.service';
   321→import logger from '../../config/logger';
   322→
   323→export async function ltiRoutes(fastify: FastifyInstance) {
   324→  // LTI launch endpoint (receives POST from Moodle) — PUBLIC, no auth middleware
   325→  fastify.post('/lti/launch', {
   326→    config: { public: true }
   327→  }, async (request, reply) => {
   328→    try {
   329→      const body = request.body as any;
   330→
   331→      logger.info('LTI launch received', {
   332→        context_id: body.context_id,
   333→        resource_link_id: body.resource_link_id,
   334→        user_id: body.user_id,
   335→        roles: body.roles
   336→      });
   337→
   338→      // CRITICAL: Validate OAuth 1.0 signature FIRST
   339→      const valid = await validateLaunch(body);
   340→      if (!valid) {
   341→        logger.error('LTI signature validation failed');
   342→        return reply.code(403).send({
   343→          success: false,
   344→          error: 'Invalid LTI signature'
   345→        });
   346→      }
   347→
   348→      // Extract LTI parameters
   349→      const contextId = body.context_id;
   350→      const resourceId = body.resource_link_id;
   351→      const userId = body.user_id;
   352→      const userEmail = body.lis_person_contact_email_primary;
   353→      const userFullname = body.lis_person_name_full;
   354→      const roles = body.roles || '';
   355→
   356→      // Parse roles (comma-separated: "Instructor,TeachingAssistant" or "Learner")
   357→      const roleList = roles.split(',').map((r: string) => r.trim());
   358→      const isInstructor = roleList.some((r: string) =>
   359→        r.includes('Instructor') || r.includes('TeachingAssistant') || r.includes('Faculty')
   360→      );
   361→
   362→      // Instructor routing: Use existing dashboard (NO LTI for teachers)
   363→      if (isInstructor) {
   364→        logger.info('Instructor launch - redirecting to dashboard');
   365→        // Instructors use existing dashboard, not LTI flow
   366→        // Return simple page with link to dashboard
   367→        return reply.type('text/html').send(`
   368→          <!DOCTYPE html>
   369→          <html>
   370→          <head><title>Instructor Access</title></head>
   371→          <body style="font-family: Arial; text-align: center; padding: 50px;">
   372→            <h2>Proctoring System</h2>
   373→            <p>Instructor access via LTI is not supported.</p>
   374→            <p>Please use the <a href="http://localhost:3000">Teacher Dashboard</a> to create proctoring rooms.</p>
   375→          </body>
   376→          </html>
   377→        `);
   378→      }
   379→
   380→      // Student routing: Join proctoring room via desktop app
   381→      logger.info('Student launch - creating room and session');
   382→
   383→      // Get or create room for this LTI context
   384→      const roomKey = `${contextId}_${resourceId}`;
   385→      const roomCode = await getOrCreateRoomForContext(roomKey, contextId, body.context_label);
   386→
   387→      // CRITICAL: Get Moodle token from user record (stored during initial Moodle auth)
   388→      // LTI doesn't have Moodle credentials, so we lookup by email
   389→      let moodleToken = null;
   390→      let moodleUserId = null;
   391→
   392→      if (userEmail) {
   393→        const userResult = await fastify.pg.query(
   394→          'SELECT id, moodle_user_id, moodle_token FROM users WHERE email = $1',
   395→          [userEmail]
   396→        );
   397→
   398→        if (userResult.rows.length > 0) {
   399→          moodleToken = userResult.rows[0].moodle_token;
   400→          moodleUserId = userResult.rows[0].moodle_user_id;
   401→          logger.info('Found Moodle token for user', { userId: userResult.rows[0].id });
   402→        } else {
   403→          logger.warn('No user found with email from LTI', { userEmail });
   404→        }
   405→      }
   406→
   407→      // Generate session token (24-hour expiry for simplicity — no refresh logic)
   408→      const token = jwt.sign({
   409→        userId: userId,
   410→        contextId: contextId,
   411→        resourceId: resourceId,
   412→        roomCode: roomCode,
   413→        role: 'student',
   414→        ltiLaunch: true,
   415→        moodleToken: moodleToken, // Include Moodle token for Quiz API calls
   416→        moodleUserId: moodleUserId,
   417→        outcomeServiceUrl: body.lis_outcome_service_url,
   418→        outcomeResultId: body.lis_result_sourcedid
   419→      }, process.env.JWT_SECRET || 'dev-secret', { expiresIn: '24h' });
   420→
   421→      // Return HTML page that launches desktop app via custom protocol
   422→      return reply.type('text/html').send(`
   423→        <!DOCTYPE html>
   424→        <html>
   425→        <head>
   426→          <title>Launching Proctoring App...</title>
   427→          <style>
   428→            body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: center; padding: 50px; background: #f5f5f5; }
   429→            .spinner { border: 4px solid #f3f3f3; border-top: 4px solid #3498db;
   430→                      border-radius: 50%; width: 40px; height: 40px;
   431→                      animation: spin 1s linear infinite; margin: 20px auto; }
   432→            @keyframes spin { 0% { transform: rotate(0deg); } 100% { transform: rotate(360deg); } }
   433→            .info { background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; max-width: 400px; margin: 20px auto; }
   434→          </style>
   435→        </head>
   436→        <body>
   437→          <div class="info">
   438→            <h2>Launching Proctoring Desktop App...</h2>
   439→            <div class="spinner"></div>
   440→            <p>Room: <strong>${roomCode}</strong></p>
   441→            <p>If the app doesn't open automatically:</p>
   442→            <p><a href="proctor://launch?room=${encodeURIComponent(roomCode)}&token=${encodeURIComponent(token)}">Click here to launch</a></p>
   443→          </div>
   444→          <script>
   445→            // Auto-launch after 2 seconds
   446→            setTimeout(() => {
   447→              window.location = 'proctor://launch?room=${encodeURIComponent(roomCode)}&token=${encodeURIComponent(token)}';
   448→            }, 2000);
   449→          </script>
   450→        </body>
   451→        </html>
   452→      `);
   453→
   454→    } catch (error) {
   455→      logger.error('LTI launch error:', error);
   456→      return reply.code(500).send({
   457→        success: false,
   458→        error: 'LTI launch failed'
   459→      });
   460→    }
   461→  });
   462→}
   463→
   464→/**
   465→ * Get or create proctoring room for LTI context
   466→ * Uses context_id + resource_link_id as unique key
   467→ */
   468→async function getOrCreateRoomForContext(
   469→  roomKey: string,
   470→  contextId: string,
   471→  contextLabel?: string
   472→): Promise<string> {
   473→  // Check if room exists
   474→  const existingRoom = await fastify.pg.query(
   475→    'SELECT room_code FROM proctoring_rooms WHERE lti_context_key = $1',
   476→    [roomKey]
   477→  );
   478→
   479→  if (existingRoom.rows.length > 0) {
   480→    logger.info('Found existing room for LTI context', { roomCode: existingRoom.rows[0].room_code });
   481→    return existingRoom.rows[0].room_code;
